The paper focuses on the physical layer of widely deployed sensors in Pervasive Computing domains, specifically on the RF-channel and ambient audio. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses distributed adaptive transmit beamforming, which involves optimisation methods, indicating that the paper could also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also mentions security applications, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The mention of the wireless interface as a sensor for environmental changes suggests that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the calculation of mathematical operations on the wireless channel, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
